Class AcceptanceRabin

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AcceptanceOmega, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<AcceptanceRabin.RabinPair>, java.util.Collection<AcceptanceRabin.RabinPair>, java.util.List<AcceptanceRabin.RabinPair>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class AcceptanceRabin
extends java.util.ArrayList<AcceptanceRabin.RabinPair>
implements AcceptanceOmega
    A Rabin acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets). This is a list of RabinPairs, which can be manipulated with the usual List interface.
    Semantics: Each Rabin pair has a state set L and K and is accepting iff L is not visited infinitely often and K is visited infinitely often: (F G !"L") & (G F "K"). The Rabin condition is accepting if at least one of the pairs is accepting.
